<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416753>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Helgenema keablei gen. n., sp. n. In all illustrations of the synlophe in transverse section the dorsal aspect of the body is oriented towards the top of the page and the left side of the nematode to the left of the page. The dorsal and ventral (numbers with superscripts) ridges are numbered, as are the lateral rays of the bursa (right rays with superscripts). A. Male, transverse section mid body; B. Female, anterior body transverse section; C. Female, anterior end lateral view; D. Spicules, anterior ends; E. Female, mid body transverse section; F. Male, gubernaculum and spicule tip, lateral view. G. Female, posterior body transverse section; H. Female, posterior end lateral view; I. Male, bursa left lobe; J. Male, bursa dorsal lobe; K. Male, bursa right lobe. Scale bars in µm: A, B, E, G, I, J, K, 25; H, 50; D, F, 12.5." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4416753/files/figure.png" .

